1
00:01:02,359 --> 00:01:02,880
Auntie Baima.

2
00:01:03,799 --> 00:01:05,120
Auntie Baima, what brings you here?

3
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:06,640
Wangdui.

4
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,120
Let me ask you something.

5
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:11,879
Must Uncle Liu's greenhouse come down?

6
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:13,680
Everyone's heard about it.

7
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:16,920
When Uncle Liu came to our village with just his bedroll,

8
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:19,040
he gave his whole heart to this village.

9
00:01:19,519 --> 00:01:20,120
Secretary.

10
00:01:21,359 --> 00:01:23,000
Back then the village was so poor,

11
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:25,400
we had no leafy greens in winter at all.

12
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,280
Uncle Liu taught us step by step,

13
00:01:29,439 --> 00:01:31,799
how to build greenhouses and lay film.

14
00:01:33,879 --> 00:01:34,439
Wangdui.

15
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:36,920
Remember the blizzard that year?

16
00:01:37,519 --> 00:01:38,719
The snow came down so heavy,

17
00:01:39,079 --> 00:01:42,519
our village's mountain roads were blocked.

18
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,640
No one had anything to eat.

19
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:46,519
It was him.

20
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,120
It was Uncle Liu.

21
00:01:48,599 --> 00:01:50,719
The vegetables from his own greenhouse,

22
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:53,040
he shared with every household.

23
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:55,760
That's how we made it through that winter.

24
00:01:58,519 --> 00:01:59,760
At the time, on behalf of the village,

25
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,120
I gave him a yak.

26
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,760
And that's how this news story came about.

27
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,599
"Vegetable Grace,"

28
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:05,719
"Yak Gratitude."

29
00:02:06,079 --> 00:02:06,719
Secretary,

30
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,159
Rural Revitalization,

31
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,520
what we're revitalizing is the industry,

32
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,199
but what we're keeping is people's hearts.

33
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,000
Uncle Liu's greenhouse,

34
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:14,680
is no longer just a few plastic sheds.

35
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,680
That's the warmth of our village.

36
00:02:17,199 --> 00:02:18,520
If for the sake of some cold, lifeless

37
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:19,479
Model Village quota,

38
00:02:20,039 --> 00:02:21,120
we tear down that warmth,

39
00:02:21,759 --> 00:02:23,840
will this still be Peach Blossom Village?

40
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,800
Yes, that's right, exactly.

41
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:25,759
We can't tear it down.

42
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:26,879
Don't tear it down, don't tear it down.

43
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,120
Auntie Baima.

44
00:02:28,599 --> 00:02:29,439
Fellow villagers,

45
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,120
everything you've said,

46
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,879
do you think it doesn't pain me too?

47
00:02:33,719 --> 00:02:35,120
Uncle Liu is our benefactor, I know.

48
00:02:35,759 --> 00:02:38,000
The four yaks everyone chipped in to buy,

49
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:39,159
I was the one who spearheaded it.

50
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:39,919
Do you all know?

51
00:02:40,719 --> 00:02:41,439
Haoran and I,

52
00:02:42,199 --> 00:02:44,039
we argued at the district over four times.

53
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:45,039
In the end...

54
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,240
Secretary! Secretary!

55
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:48,439
Folks,

56
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,080
take a look.

57
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,240
Over there,

58
00:02:53,319 --> 00:02:54,479
the ancient riverbed protection zone,

59
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:55,879
that red line can't be crossed.

60
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:58,879
That whole area,

61
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,479
is a high-voltage power line corridor.

62
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,080
Way too dangerous.

63
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,039
And up ahead,

64
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,159
there are geological hazard zones.

65
00:03:07,879 --> 00:03:09,080
Who would dare build a road there?

66
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:12,599
The Secretary and I,

67
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:13,680
we worked overtime every day.

68
00:03:14,479 --> 00:03:15,840
We revised the blueprints dozens of times,

69
00:03:16,919 --> 00:03:18,439
We really can't go around it, we...

70
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:20,800
Uncle Liu's greenhouse,

71
00:03:22,479 --> 00:03:23,719
it sits right on this choke point,

72
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:25,960
blocking the village's main artery, folks.

73
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:30,439
Uncle Liu,

74
00:03:32,919 --> 00:03:34,479
think about the kids in our village.

75
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,879
We tried hard to bring these educated kids

76
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:38,639
back home,

77
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,639
We're counting on them to run the experimental fields,

78
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,719
counting on them to lead us to prosperity.

79
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:45,840
Without the road, equipment can't get in,

80
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,240
and good products can't get out.

81
00:03:47,639 --> 00:03:49,400
Even if they grow nuggets of gold,

82
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,039
they'll just rot in the field.

83
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,479
And when that happens,

84
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:54,960
these kids will leave again.

85
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:00,919
Uncle,

86
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,439
Say what you will, scold me, it's fine.

87
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:07,520
If I could route the road elsewhere,

88
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,520
I wouldn't touch your greenhouse.

89
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,319
I really wouldn't.

90
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,599
But to improve the whole village's life,

91
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:15,759
this road,

92
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,279
we have to build it this way.

93
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:00,680
Uncle Liu.

94
00:05:02,439 --> 00:05:03,079
You're here, dear.

95
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:04,839
How's your leg?

96
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:06,879
Much better.

97
00:05:07,199 --> 00:05:08,720
The medicine Zhaxi gave me works well.

98
00:05:09,839 --> 00:05:10,480
That kid.

99
00:05:11,439 --> 00:05:12,480
That's about all he's good for.

100
00:05:13,959 --> 00:05:16,000
He's good at plenty of things.

101
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,720
Putting in a good word for him already?

102
00:05:20,439 --> 00:05:21,360
Uncle Liu.

103
00:05:23,759 --> 00:05:24,639
You need something from me?

104
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,360
No, nothing.

105
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,120
Just passing by.

106
00:05:30,519 --> 00:05:31,360
Came to see you.

107
00:05:32,279 --> 00:05:34,040
What's to see in a grumpy old man like me?

108
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:39,920
Uncle Liu,

109
00:05:40,279 --> 00:05:40,959
do you still remember?

110
00:05:41,399 --> 00:05:42,600
When I was little, I'd always

111
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,000
run off to your greenhouse.

112
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:47,040
I remember.

113
00:05:48,399 --> 00:05:49,120
How could I forget?

114
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:50,839
Back then,

115
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,600
you'd be there growing vegetables.

116
00:05:52,839 --> 00:05:53,480
And I'd ask you,

117
00:05:53,879 --> 00:05:54,920
"Uncle Liu, Uncle Liu,

118
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:56,879
how do these vegetables grow?"

119
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,920
You said they grow on their own.

120
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,439
Then I asked you,

121
00:06:00,759 --> 00:06:03,240
"Why do yours grow better than others?"

122
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,879
You said if you're good to them,

123
00:06:05,879 --> 00:06:06,839
they grow well.

124
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,519
Back when you asked me all that,

125
00:06:10,519 --> 00:06:12,399
I really couldn't answer.

126
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,800
How would I know why?

127
00:06:14,319 --> 00:06:15,240
All I knew was,

128
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,240
these vegetables,

129
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,360
these crops,

130
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,720
if you're good to them,

131
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,680
if you put your heart into them,

132
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,600
they'll be good to you too.

133
00:06:20,759 --> 00:06:21,600
They'll grow well.

134
00:06:24,519 --> 00:06:25,839
But thinking about it now,

135
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,639
everything you said makes sense.

136
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:31,240
You said being good to them

137
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:32,199
makes them grow well.

138
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,959
That's the way of the land.

139
00:06:35,279 --> 00:06:36,279
Growing on their own,

140
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,000
is the instinct of life.

141
00:06:40,439 --> 00:06:41,680
The instinct of life?

142
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,759
I don't get it.

143
00:06:44,199 --> 00:06:45,680
The same words,

144
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,240
from my mouth are just country talk;

145
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,759
from yours, it's profound knowledge.

146
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,240
A true Doctor indeed.

147
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,240
But you know what?

148
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,959
The reason I went away to study,

149
00:06:55,959 --> 00:06:57,000
all the way to becoming a Doctor,

150
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:58,360
it's all because of you.

151
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,040
What?

152
00:07:01,079 --> 00:07:01,759
Because of me?

153
00:07:04,879 --> 00:07:06,240
As a kid, I always wondered,

154
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,560
how Uncle Liu was so amazing.

155
00:07:09,079 --> 00:07:11,040
When the soil needs watering,

156
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:13,160
when the seedlings need fertilizing,

157
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,519
he could tell at a glance.

158
00:07:16,279 --> 00:07:18,720
Later I went to the big city,

159
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,360
entered the lab,

160
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,560
looked at all the data,

161
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,439
all those instruments,

162
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,639
and then I realized,

163
00:07:25,959 --> 00:07:27,439
it's actually the same as what you said.

164
00:07:28,079 --> 00:07:28,680
The same?

165
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:30,680
No way.

166
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,120
Yours is high tech,

167
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,720
mine's just old country tricks.

168
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,800
How could they be the same?

169
00:07:34,959 --> 00:07:35,800
They are the same.

170
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,439
We're both trying to figure out

171
00:07:39,639 --> 00:07:41,360
what's going on with the soil,

172
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,199
how the seedlings grow.

173
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,399
It's just that you use your hands,

174
00:07:46,639 --> 00:07:47,680
and I use instruments.

175
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:49,920
You use your eyes,

176
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,560
and I use data.

177
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,360
Dr. Meiduo,

178
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,319
you can't praise me like this.

179
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,040
I'll get a big head if you do.

180
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,759
I can't handle it, I really can't.

181
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:02,920
I'm being serious.

182
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,920
I've actually always wanted to ask you

183
00:08:08,319 --> 00:08:09,879
why you chose to come here originally.

184
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,319
My dad told me

185
00:08:12,319 --> 00:08:14,879
you had a comfortable life in your youth.

186
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,160
What made you lose your mind

187
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,319
and grow veggies in our mountain valley?

188
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,199
Lose my mind?

189
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,639
I'd say I finally found it.

190
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:24,920
There was this one time,

191
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,000
just by chance,

192
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,519
I came to Xizang.

193
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,279
The moment I got off the bus,

194
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:33,240
the mountains here were in the clouds,

195
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:35,720
the water here was green,

196
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:39,679
and the sky was the deepest blue.

197
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,440
I was completely stunned.

198
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,360
Wasn't this exactly the home of my dreams?

199
00:08:49,039 --> 00:08:49,600
Dear,

200
00:08:50,399 --> 00:08:52,279
I grew up in the countryside myself.

201
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:53,960
And later on,

202
00:08:54,639 --> 00:08:55,679
I moved to the city.

203
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:57,799
But living in the city,

204
00:08:57,960 --> 00:09:01,159
my heart always felt empty.

205
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:02,519
But when I came here,

206
00:09:03,399 --> 00:09:05,759
the mountains, the water, the people here,

207
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,000
they filled the empty places in my heart

208
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,519
all the way up.

209
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,799
So that's why you chose to stay.

210
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:12,759
Right.

211
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:16,039
And this greenhouse of mine,

212
00:09:16,759 --> 00:09:18,480
it wasn't built the moment I arrived.

213
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,440
It was with these two hands,

214
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,720
that I built it piece by piece.

215
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:25,480
And the folks in the village,

216
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:27,759
Yangjin,

217
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,000
Duoji,

218
00:09:29,759 --> 00:09:30,679
Zhuoma.

219
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,440
You know all of them.

220
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,399
Working with me,

221
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:36,960
eating together,

222
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,360
living life together.

223
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:42,559
And I thought,

224
00:09:43,759 --> 00:09:44,480
I thought,

225
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:46,879
isn't this the life I wanted?

226
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:49,759
So,

227
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,960
it's not the greenhouse you can't leave,

228
00:09:54,039 --> 00:09:54,960
it's the people here.

229
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:56,679
Right.

230
00:09:57,759 --> 00:09:59,320
You hit the nail on the head with that.

231
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:00,720
Uncle Liu,

232
00:10:01,799 --> 00:10:03,279
whatever choice you make,

233
00:10:03,639 --> 00:10:04,480
I'll support you.

234
00:10:05,279 --> 00:10:07,000
If you really want to save the greenhouse,

235
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,720
we'll figure it out together.

236
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:14,840
So,

237
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:16,639
don't overthink it.

238
00:10:17,519 --> 00:10:18,559
Just think it through,

239
00:10:19,399 --> 00:10:21,000
why you came here in the first place.

240
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:22,960
Once you've thought it through,

241
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,440
whatever you decide will be right.

242
00:10:28,559 --> 00:10:29,279
Uncle Liu.

243
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:31,960
Uncle Liu.

244
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,600
No matter what you end up choosing,

245
00:10:37,279 --> 00:10:38,320
I'll be right there with you.

246
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:41,039
Okay.

247
00:11:16,279 --> 00:11:17,080
It's no use!

248
00:11:17,399 --> 00:11:18,399
The wind's too strong!

249
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:19,879
I can't hold it down!

250
00:11:20,279 --> 00:11:21,399
Hurry, go find some rocks!

251
00:11:21,399 --> 00:11:22,639
If these seedlings get ruined,

252
00:11:22,639 --> 00:11:24,159
all my experiment data will be lost.

253
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,279
Zhaxi!

254
00:11:26,279 --> 00:11:27,240
What are you two doing?

255
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:27,919
Uncle Liu!

256
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,039
Blocking it like this

257
00:11:29,039 --> 00:11:29,919
isn't gonna do a damn thing!

258
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,519
Come on, spread this plastic sheet out.

259
00:11:33,279 --> 00:11:34,159
Come on, pull it open.

260
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,080
Watch me.

261
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,080
I'll teach you how to tie a clove hitch.

262
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:42,759
Here.

263
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,080
Slip it through.

264
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:45,600
Loop it around.

265
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,240
Then pull it tight.

266
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:48,639
See that?

267
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:49,799
Zhaxi!

268
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:51,919
Go grab a stool.

269
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:52,559
Okay.

270
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:55,200
Go!

271
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:56,639
Toss it to that side.

272
00:11:57,879 --> 00:11:58,919
Tie it up there.

273
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,639
Come on, pull it tight.

274
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,399
Zhaxi!

275
00:12:09,679 --> 00:12:10,240
Coming!

276
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:10,919
Ready?

277
00:12:11,759 --> 00:12:12,279
Get up there.

278
00:12:12,639 --> 00:12:13,480
Pull it up.

279
00:12:19,759 --> 00:12:20,879
Tighter, tighter!

280
00:12:22,639 --> 00:12:23,600
Pull it tight.

281
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:33,559
Press it down again.

282
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:35,519
Qianqian!

283
00:12:36,879 --> 00:12:37,519
What?

284
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,960
Road's closed, the veggies can't get in.

285
00:12:41,639 --> 00:12:42,279
Where?

286
00:12:42,919 --> 00:12:43,799
At the village committee.

287
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,559
